steps.instruction:
### Ingredients
- Vanilla-Butternut Flavor is *optional*
- You can toast the 1/2 cup of pecans that will be going in the pie
    1. Dice the 1/2 cup of pecans
    2. Preheat your oven to 350F
    3. Put into the oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until they reach a mahogany color
    - You can also toast in a toaster oven, or shake the nuts on a hot skillet 
- You *can* substitute a couple of tablespoons of the milk for the same amount of rum or whiskey 
- You can make it with a chocolate crust, just search for chocolate crust
- You can add some chocolate chips into the batter or more simply a single even layer of chocolate chips on the bottom of the crust
    - Semisweet or bittersweet is apparently better contrast to the caramel taste of the pecans
- A sprinkle of salt on the top of the pie filling either before or after baking is good. Large flake sea salt *looks* better if you want to flex on Instagram 

### Prep
- Either [make](http://67.9.187.149:8080/view/recipe/124) your pie crust or buy one
- Whisk the eggs briefly, just to combine 
- Dice the 1/2 of pecans
- Half the 1 cup of pecans 


### Steps 
1. Preheat oven to 375F
2. Roll out the pastry and place it in a greased 9" pie plate, flute the edges 
3. Melt the butter
4. Set the butter aside to cool
5. In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar and salt
6. Add the milk and eggs
7. Beat well 
8. Stir in the vinegar, vanilla and flavoring (if using), then the butter and diced pecans
9. Pour the mixture into the crust
10. Put the halved pecans on the top of the pie 
11. Bake for 47 to 50 minutes
    - When done the top will be puffed up and set
    - The center should just barely wobble when you jiggle it
12. Remove pie from oven
13. Allow the pie to cool completely
